===date:Tue Aug 26 18:05:18 2003
===message:I agree with a lot of what Jade says, however... weren't most Americans descendants of immigrants?  My parent's parents came from Austria and Germany and came to New York through Ellis island in the early 1900's.  So aren't I a result of their immigration?  Aren't I an American because of it?  We should embrace immigrants- remember the "melting" pot?  As for the Chinese, of course they were brought here in the thousands to do a job and when the job was over, stayed on to try to find work in an economic depression.  This exacerbated the already skewed prejudices people had.  I grew up in New York and I remember when waves of Puerto Ricans came into the city...it seemed that there were more than could get work.  As depicted in Leonard Bernsteins "West Side Story", the prejudices were often totally unsubstantiated.  Perhaps that contributed to the culture of the Californian's disdain for the Chinese.  
=========yorg=========
