In general it does seem that Americans strongly feel that immigrants should easily adapt to as you called it the "American Ideal" I agree with you Americans seem to display opposition when immigrants don't fit in to their American role and the immigrants display their differences. When considering the transition that immigrants encounter I can't even imagine how it would feel to arrive in an unfamiliar land with a completely different language, customs, and traditions. I think a lot of Americans feel that immigrants come to enforce their own way of life, but I think the immigrants aren't simply welcomed to assimilate into the American life and so they retreat to the only way they know thus establishing their own communities, identities, etc.

